## Monitoring and Maintenance

### Quarterly Review

**Every 3 months, audit all commands:**

```bash
# Generate budget report
for cmd in .claude/commands/*.md; do
  chars=$(wc -c < "$cmd")
  name=$(basename "$cmd" .md)
  status="✅"
  [ $chars -gt 15000 ] && status="❌ OVER"
  [ $chars -gt 12000 ] && [ $chars -le 15000 ] && status="⚠️ HIGH"
  echo "$name: $chars chars - $status"
done | sort -t: -k2 -n

# Identify refactoring candidates
# Commands over 12K should be reviewed
```

**Review criteria:**
- [ ] Any commands over 15K? (refactor immediately)
- [ ] Any commands over 12K? (plan refactoring)
- [ ] Command growth rate (comparing to previous quarter)
- [ ] New commands following pattern? (lean by design)
- [ ] Token efficiency maintained? (monitor main conversation usage)

